# Traditional Chinese (zh-TW) Localization Rule

## Rule
**All user-facing text in the WebUI must be in Traditional Chinese (zh-TW).** Code, comments, and variable names remain in English.

## Brand Name
- **Brand Name**: 財經快摘 (TrendBrief)
- Use "財經快摘" for Chinese contexts
- Use "TrendBrief" as the English brand name when needed

## Scope

### Translate to zh-TW:
- UI labels and button text
- Page titles and headings
- Navigation menu items
- Placeholder text in inputs
- Error messages shown to users
- Tooltips and help text
- Chart labels and legends
- Table headers
- Modal titles and content
- Empty state messages
- Loading messages

### Keep in English:
- Code (variables, functions, classes)
- Comments in code
- Console logs
- Technical error messages (for debugging)
- API endpoint names
- File names
- CSS class names
- Data attributes

